  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to see whether intensive smoking intervention on the day of
      operation can reduce per- and postoperative complications in patients operated for acute
      ischaemic disease compared to control group with no intervention.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
